The Scorched Wastes: Collapsed Administrative District

Bureau of Eastern Routes, Historical Threat Division
Filed under: Institutional Failure, Undead Persistence, Cautionary Record

Our older ledgers refer to this region as the Meridian Intake March:
a managed corridor of toll pavilions, cistern regulators, and charter
stations. We held tariff agreements with the Intake offices. Our
clerks exchanged correspondence with their clerks. We recognized them
as colleagues in administration.

They are all dead now. Some of them are still working.

The Ninth Meridian Rite exceeded institutional competence in ways
our Bureau has classified as a cascading administrative failure of
the first order. Heat surged through channels meant for water. The
sustained burn wave glassed dunes, collapsed structures, and
produced undead administrative persistence.

The Charter Remnants unsettle our clerks most. Descendants of
intake clerks and ration auditors -- some living survivalists, others
undead functionaries still demanding documents and issuing
citations before attacking when proper paperwork is not produced.
They stamp, witness, seal, and kill.

The Reckoning faction has circulated this in broadsheets: "What
separates a Midgaard gate clerk from a Wastes revenant? The
revenant's institution collapsed. Ours has not. Yet." The Continuity
faction finds this offensive. The Bureau finds it technically
precise.

The Dune Host Reavers inherited route knowledge from ruined intake
records, hoarding water containers and legal tablets equally. The
Synod Eclipse Cells stage mock tribunals and witness-burning rites.
Both are parasites on a dead host's nervous system. Below them,
faultline entities manifest near dry governor mechanisms -- our
advisories classify these as hazard: environmental, origin:
institutional residue.

The Wastes share a thermal origin with the Saltglass Reach. The
same pulse that created this burn scar propagated eastward at
attenuated intensity. We note this coupling in our risk models.

The final assessment line in every Bureau report reads the same:
Law persists after legitimacy dies. Water memory outlives water
presence. Administrative tools become ritual weapons under scarcity.
This is not foreign. This is familiar. That is what makes it a
cautionary record of the highest priority.
