The Scorched Wastes -- Quarantine Ledger Exclusion Brief

The Quarantine Ledger maintains a standing exclusion order on all
cargo from the Scorched Wastes. Classification: Collapsed
Attestation Zone, Tier Four -- the highest hazard designation our
system recognizes. The Wastes are not merely dangerous terrain.
They are a dead trade district still issuing documents.

The Ledger Houses remember what the Wastes were: the Meridian
Intake March, a corridor of toll pavilions and charter stations.
In its functioning era, Mafdet received goods from the Intake March
with clean provenance. Then the Ninth Meridian Rite failed, and
the burn wave turned a trade corridor into a glass-and-ash necropolis.

What concerns our Hazard Scribes is the persistence of process
without legitimacy. The undead Charter Remnants -- former intake
clerks -- still demand documents and issue citations at checkpoints
connecting to no functioning authority. This is oath-breaking of
the deepest kind: law's form maintained after its substance has
died. The Shrine of the First Claw recognizes no oath sworn to a
dead institution.

The Dune Host Reavers mimic attestation but carry no authority
our Ledger Houses accept. When Reaver-handled cargo reaches the
Saltglass Reach, our assessors strip all prior documentation and
re-attest from scratch. The cost falls on the carrier.

The Synod Eclipse Cells conducting mock tribunals and witness-
burning rites are the Quarantine Ledger's worst-case scenario
made real: religious authority filling the void of collapsed civic
process. Their recut inscriptions occasionally appear on cargo
containers reaching our port. We destroy them on sight.

The Wastes share origin with our own Saltglass Reach -- the same
thermal pulse, attenuated by distance, created our glass flats.
What burned the Wastes glazed our doorstep.

Every guardian-name sworn at the Shrine carries an implicit clause:
we will not become what the Wastes became. Process without
accountability. Oaths enforced by the dead against the living.
The Quarantine Ledger exists because the Wastes proved that
documentation alone is not enough. Someone living must stand
behind it.

